---
import ToolPage from '../layouts/ToolPage.astro';
---
<ToolPage
  title="MCP Config Generator & Validator, build claude_desktop_config.json | KB Cafe"
  description="Build a valid Model Context Protocol (MCP) server config for Claude Desktop, or paste an existing one to validate it. Free, fully client-side, nothing is uploaded."
  path="/mcp-config-generator"
  eyebrow="AI Explained · Tool"
  h1="MCP Config Generator"
  tagline="Build a valid MCP server block for claude_desktop_config.json from a simple form, or paste an existing config to validate it. Runs entirely in your browser."
>
  <div class="row mc-mode" id="mode">
    <button class="chip active" data-m="build">Build</button>
    <button class="chip" data-m="validate">Validate</button>
  </div>

  <!-- BUILD -->
  <div id="build-view">
    <div id="servers"></div>
    <div class="row" style="margin:14px 0 6px"><button class="btn ghost" id="add">+ Add server</button></div>
    <div class="pane">
      <div class="pane-label"><span>claude_desktop_config.json</span></div>
      <textarea id="out" class="ta" readonly spellcheck="false"></textarea>
    </div>
    <button class="btn-copy" id="copy" type="button" style="margin-top:12px"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="9" y="9" width="11" height="11" rx="2"/><path d="M5 15V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10"/></svg><span class="lbl">Copy config</span></button>
  </div>

  <!-- VALIDATE -->
  <div id="validate-view" style="display:none">
    <div class="pane">
      <div class="pane-label"><span>Paste a config to validate</span><button class="link-btn" id="vsample">sample</button></div>
      <textarea id="vin" class="ta" spellcheck="false" placeholder="Paste your claude_desktop_config.json…"></textarea>
    </div>
    <div class="mc-findings" id="findings"></div>
  </div>
  <p class="status" id="status"></p>

  <Fragment slot="explainer">
    <h2>What this builds</h2>
    <p>
      The <a href="/what-is-mcp">Model Context Protocol</a> lets an AI app connect to external tools through a
      standard config. For Claude Desktop that config lives in <code>claude_desktop_config.json</code>, and every
      server goes under an <code>mcpServers</code> object with a <strong>command</strong> to launch it, its
      <strong>args</strong>, and any <strong>env</strong> variables (like API keys). A single misplaced comma or a
      string where an array belongs stops every server from loading, so this tool builds the shape for you and
      validates one you already have.
    </p>
    <h3>The shape of a server</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>command</strong>, the executable, often <code>npx</code>, <code>node</code>, <code>uvx</code>, or <code>python</code>.</li>
      <li><strong>args</strong>, an <em>array</em> of strings passed to the command (one per line in the form).</li>
      <li><strong>env</strong>, optional key/value pairs, the usual home for secrets like <code>API_KEY</code>.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="note">
      This generates and checks the JSON locally, nothing is uploaded, so it is safe to paste a config that
      contains keys. That said, treat real secrets carefully and prefer environment references where you can.
    </p>

    <h2>FAQ</h2>
    <details class="faq"><summary>Where does this file go?</summary>
      <p>On macOS, <code>~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json</code>; on Windows, <code>%APPDATA%\Claude\claude_desktop_config.json</code>. Restart Claude Desktop after editing.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq"><summary>Does the validator run my servers?</summary>
      <p>No. It only checks the JSON structure (valid syntax, an <code>mcpServers</code> object, a string <code>command</code>, an array <code>args</code>, and object <code>env</code>). It never executes anything.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq"><summary>Is my config uploaded?</summary>
      <p>No. Generation and validation are entirely client-side, so the config and any keys in it stay on your device.</p>
    </details>

    <h3>Related</h3>
    <p>Read <a href="/what-is-mcp">what MCP is</a> and how it relates to <a href="/what-is-tool-calling">tool calling</a>, or browse <a href="/ai">AI Explained</a>.</p>
  </Fragment>
</ToolPage>

<style>
  .link-btn{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.06em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--coral);background:none;border:0;cursor:pointer}
  .link-btn:hover{color:var(--coral-deep);text-decoration:underline}
  .mc-mode{margin-bottom:18px}
  .srv{border:1.5px solid var(--line);border-radius:16px;background:var(--cream);padding:16px;margin-bottom:14px}
  .srv-top{display:flex;gap:12px;align-items:center;margin-bottom:12px}
  .srv-top input{flex:1;min-width:0}
  .mc-in{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:13.5px;border:1.5px solid var(--line);border-radius:10px;padding:9px 11px;background:var(--paper);color:var(--ink);outline:0}
  .mc-in:focus{border-color:var(--ink)}
  .mc-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:12px}
  .mc-field{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px}
  .mc-field label{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:10.5px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-soft)}
  .mc-field textarea{min-height:84px;resize:vertical;font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:13px;line-height:1.5;border:1.5px solid var(--line);border-radius:10px;padding:9px 11px;background:var(--paper);color:var(--ink);outline:0}
  .mc-field textarea:focus{border-color:var(--ink)}
  .srv-rm{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--coral-deep);background:none;border:0;cursor:pointer;white-space:nowrap}
  .srv-rm:hover{text-decoration:underline}
  .ta{min-height:180px}
  .pane{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:9px;margin-top:4px}
  .pane-label{display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-soft)}

  .mc-findings{margin-top:18px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:9px}
  .find{display:flex;gap:11px;align-items:flex-start;border:1.5px solid var(--line);border-radius:12px;padding:12px 14px;background:var(--cream);font-size:14px;line-height:1.45}
  .find .ic{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-weight:800;font-size:13px;flex-shrink:0}
  .find.err{border-color:var(--coral-deep)} .find.err .ic{color:var(--coral-deep)}
  .find.warn .ic{color:var(--orange)} .find.ok{border-color:#2f7d32} .find.ok .ic{color:#2f7d32}
  .find code{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:12.5px;background:var(--paper-2);padding:1px 5px;border-radius:5px}
  @media(max-width:620px){.mc-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
</style>

<script is:inline>
  const $ = (id) => document.getElementById(id);
  const KNOWN = ['command', 'args', 'env', 'cwd', 'type', 'url', 'headers'];

  // ---------- BUILD ----------
  let servers = [];
  let seed = 0;
  function addServer(s) {
    servers.push(Object.assign({ id: ++seed, name: '', command: 'npx', args: '', env: '' }, s || {}));
    renderServers();
  }
  function renderServers() {
    const box = $('servers'); box.innerHTML = '';
    servers.forEach((s) => {
      const el = document.createElement('div'); el.className = 'srv';
      el.innerHTML = `
        <div class="srv-top">
          <input class="mc-in f-name" placeholder="server name (e.g. filesystem)" value="${escAttr(s.name)}" />
          <input class="mc-in f-cmd" placeholder="command" value="${escAttr(s.command)}" style="max-width:160px" />
          <button class="srv-rm">remove</button>
        </div>
        <div class="mc-grid">
          <div class="mc-field"><label>args (one per line)</label><textarea class="f-args" spellcheck="false" placeholder="-y&#10;@modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem&#10;/path/to/dir">${escHtml(s.args)}</textarea></div>
          <div class="mc-field"><label>env (KEY=value per line)</label><textarea class="f-env" spellcheck="false" placeholder="API_KEY=sk-...">${escHtml(s.env)}</textarea></div>
        </div>`;
      el.querySelector('.f-name').addEventListener('input', (e) => { s.name = e.target.value; build(); });
      el.querySelector('.f-cmd').addEventListener('input', (e) => { s.command = e.target.value; build(); });
      el.querySelector('.f-args').addEventListener('input', (e) => { s.args = e.target.value; build(); });
      el.querySelector('.f-env').addEventListener('input', (e) => { s.env = e.target.value; build(); });
      el.querySelector('.srv-rm').addEventListener('click', () => { servers = servers.filter(x => x.id !== s.id); renderServers(); build(); });
      box.appendChild(el);
    });
  }
  function build() {
    const obj = { mcpServers: {} };
    servers.forEach((s) => {
      const name = s.name.trim() || 'unnamed';
      const entry = { command: s.command.trim() };
      const args = s.args.split('\n').map(a => a.trim()).filter(Boolean);
      entry.args = args;
      const env = {};
      s.env.split('\n').map(l => l.trim()).filter(Boolean).forEach(l => {
        const i = l.indexOf('='); if (i > 0) env[l.slice(0, i).trim()] = l.slice(i + 1).trim();
      });
      if (Object.keys(env).length) entry.env = env;
      obj.mcpServers[name] = entry;
    });
    $('out').value = JSON.stringify(obj, null, 2);
  }
  function escAttr(s) { return String(s).replace(/&/g, '&amp;').replace(/"/g, '&quot;'); }
  function escHtml(s) { return String(s).replace(/&/g, '&amp;').replace(/</g, '&lt;').replace(/>/g, '&gt;'); }

  // ---------- VALIDATE ----------
  const SAMPLE_CFG = `{
  "mcpServers": {
    "filesystem": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem", "/Users/me/docs"],
      "env": { "LOG_LEVEL": "info" }
    }
  }
}`;
  function finding(kind, msg) { return `<div class="find ${kind}"><span class="ic">${kind === 'err' ? '✕' : kind === 'warn' ? '!' : '✓'}</span><span>${msg}</span></div>`; }
  function validate() {
    const raw = $('vin').value.trim(); const box = $('findings');
    if (!raw) { box.innerHTML = ''; return; }
    let data;
    try { data = JSON.parse(raw); }
    catch (e) { box.innerHTML = finding('err', 'Invalid JSON: ' + escHtml((e.message || '').split('\n')[0])); return; }
    const out = [];
    if (typeof data !== 'object' || data === null || Array.isArray(data)) { box.innerHTML = finding('err', 'Top level must be a JSON object.'); return; }
    let root = data;
    if (!('mcpServers' in data)) {
      // maybe they pasted just the servers map
      const looksLikeServers = Object.values(data).every(v => v && typeof v === 'object' && ('command' in v || 'url' in v));
      if (looksLikeServers && Object.keys(data).length) { out.push(finding('warn', 'No <code>mcpServers</code> wrapper found, validating the object as the servers map. Wrap it in <code>{ "mcpServers": { … } }</code>.')); root = { mcpServers: data }; }
      else { box.innerHTML = finding('err', 'Missing <code>mcpServers</code> object.'); return; }
    }
    const servers = root.mcpServers;
    if (typeof servers !== 'object' || servers === null || Array.isArray(servers)) { box.innerHTML = finding('err', '<code>mcpServers</code> must be an object keyed by server name.'); return; }
    const names = Object.keys(servers);
    if (!names.length) out.push(finding('warn', '<code>mcpServers</code> is empty, no servers will load.'));
    names.forEach((name) => {
      const s = servers[name];
      if (typeof s !== 'object' || s === null || Array.isArray(s)) { out.push(finding('err', `Server <code>${escHtml(name)}</code> must be an object.`)); return; }
      const remote = 'url' in s && !('command' in s);
      if (remote) {
        if (typeof s.url !== 'string' || !s.url) out.push(finding('err', `<code>${escHtml(name)}</code>: remote server needs a string <code>url</code>.`));
      } else {
        if (!('command' in s)) out.push(finding('err', `<code>${escHtml(name)}</code>: missing <code>command</code>.`));
        else if (typeof s.command !== 'string' || !s.command.trim()) out.push(finding('err', `<code>${escHtml(name)}</code>: <code>command</code> must be a non-empty string.`));
        if (!('args' in s)) out.push(finding('warn', `<code>${escHtml(name)}</code>: no <code>args</code> (defaults to none), usually you want an array.`));
        else if (!Array.isArray(s.args)) out.push(finding('err', `<code>${escHtml(name)}</code>: <code>args</code> must be an array of strings.`));
        else if (!s.args.every(a => typeof a === 'string')) out.push(finding('err', `<code>${escHtml(name)}</code>: every item in <code>args</code> must be a string.`));
      }
      if ('env' in s) {
        if (typeof s.env !== 'object' || s.env === null || Array.isArray(s.env)) out.push(finding('err', `<code>${escHtml(name)}</code>: <code>env</code> must be an object.`));
        else if (!Object.values(s.env).every(v => typeof v === 'string')) out.push(finding('warn', `<code>${escHtml(name)}</code>: <code>env</code> values should be strings.`));
      }
      Object.keys(s).filter(k => !KNOWN.includes(k)).forEach(k => out.push(finding('warn', `<code>${escHtml(name)}</code>: unknown key <code>${escHtml(k)}</code>.`)));
    });
    const hasErr = out.some(f => f.includes('find err'));
    if (!hasErr) out.unshift(finding('ok', `Valid. ${names.length} server${names.length === 1 ? '' : 's'} configured.`));
    box.innerHTML = out.join('');
  }

  // ---------- mode switch ----------
  $('mode').addEventListener('click', (e) => {
    const b = e.target.closest('.chip'); if (!b) return;
    document.querySelectorAll('#mode .chip').forEach(c => c.classList.remove('active')); b.classList.add('active');
    const build = b.dataset.m === 'build';
    $('build-view').style.display = build ? '' : 'none';
    $('validate-view').style.display = build ? 'none' : '';
  });
  $('add').addEventListener('click', () => addServer());
  $('copy').addEventListener('click', async () => {
    if (!$('out').value) return;
    try { await navigator.clipboard.writeText($('out').value); } catch { $('out').select(); document.execCommand('copy'); }
    const b = $('copy'); b.classList.add('done'); b.querySelector('.lbl').textContent = 'Copied!';
    setTimeout(() => { b.classList.remove('done'); b.querySelector('.lbl').textContent = 'Copy config'; }, 1600);
  });
  $('vin').addEventListener('input', validate);
  $('vsample').addEventListener('click', () => { $('vin').value = SAMPLE_CFG; validate(); });

  // seed one example server
  addServer({ name: 'filesystem', command: 'npx', args: '-y\n@modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem\n/Users/me/docs', env: '' });
  build();
</script>
